{"key":"post-12458614","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12458614</id>\n<content>Lime can 'pasteurize', not sterilize.&amp;nbsp; However, it's inferior to heat pasteurization.&amp;nbsp; Soak the straw in water for 12 hours, or 2 hours if you use dish soap.&amp;nbsp; Then, move the straw to 140F to 160F water for one hour. You can add a cup of hydrated lime to the pasteurization water for added benefit, but it's optional. Drain, and use when cooled.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12503380</next>\n<prev>12457786</prev>\n<first>12457786</first>\n<last>12503380</last>\n<when>1272294797</when>\n<utime>04/26/10 06:13 PM</utime>\n</post>"}